issue.title: Prevent domain field evaluation from failing when: (1) the domain is …
issue.body:
I have some code like this:
# In Python:
class AccountPaymentOrder(models.Model):
    _inherit = "account.payment.order"
    json_allowed_journals_domain = fields.Char(related="payment_mode_id.json_allowed_journals_domain")
# In XML:
<xpath expr="//field[@name='journal_id']" position="attributes">
    <attribute name="domain">json_allowed_journals_domain</attribute>
</xpath>

And form loading was failing when creating a new record, because the fiels payment_mode_id was not yet set.

This pull request fixes this:
Prevent domain field evaluation from failing when: (1) the domain is given
by a related field and (2) the path to the target field is not yet
traversable. In this cases, reading the field from javascript code will
yield false. This fix makes the frontend assume a "[]" domain whenever the
field refered to in domain="" attribute contains a false value.

issue.body:
Sale_outstanding add-on adds sum_outstanding field to sale.order model, and displays it in the sale order form view.
The field content is the sum of the invoiced amounts linked to the sale order.

**Test scenario:**
- basic test:
  - create a sale order with several products
  - invoice a part of the global amount, open it (invoice_lines must match with order_lines)
  => sum_outstanding field content is the amount invoiced
  - create a new invoice, open it
  => sum_outstanding field content is the sum of the two previous invoices

issue.body:
Finish  #2 

### Clean and refactor

- [x] some clean. remove commented code :  https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/9582751d0e9db6de1706527209665fd322703810, remove "cagnotte" word : https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/8100b55f836a91adf5853f2af20b9cc84c8a99ea remove ``openupgradelib`` dependency : https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/6f6392ddcaac00eefb52c792e344760f28215914
- [x] rename file that contains view to fit OCA convention. https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/6de4402b564b34749fb827efd1ed577520c402c0 https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/10acc32dfb60035004117186cc0de92132e041d7
- [x] remove duplicated views for ``account.move`` and ``account.move.line`` https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/c94432c55cecf4fa9aedbd1548ed38626190c7bc https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/b49885ab1cd9375ee0b26a1afd4d84065a0d3aae  
- [x] refactor test functions to factorize code. https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/2887ce5b37b19d0621c2aaf17c54d0fce968e162
- [x] rename ``no_anonymous`` field into ``automatic_nominative_creation`` because the description is better, to have the possibility to introduce a new field ``only_nominative`` and to prevent double negation : https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/0d0e39214ae9cb96174abc0e6dc397c2a6bad933 (openupgrade script included).

### UX Improvment
- [x] add domain on product field of ``account.wallet.type`` https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/73f2bb4dc892e7f510b5dce50e3ae86f3e75a10f

### Bugfixes
- [x] in initial version, wallet balance are computed on draft, posted and cancel account move lines. With that patch, only 'posted' move lines impact balance. https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/6b8c6d794ffce550c9810bd7c3ddd5f6b9f0b49e
- [x] allow to select wallet on payment refund https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/f009d9030b7923067fe809b4ba3fb2b08f6e1e1e

### Add Feature
- [x] add field ``only_nominative`` on ``account.wallet.type`` to prevent wallet without partner defined. https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/e8c4fa380283197ede73bdac8202882cfd6eeb88
- [x] allow to select wallet on the wizard ``account.payment.register`` https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/223e7ef1ec464942ac3b7016f06f5a03da8ede91 
- [x] make credit note wallet feature working in a multi company and or multi wallet type context https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/c23d67b2bfb43a0c1d20ccb136aa921483e4b94e

- basic test:
  - create a sale order with several products
  - invoice a part of the global amount, open it (invoice_lines must match with order_lines)
  => sum_outstanding field content is the amount invoiced
  - create a new invoice, open it
  => sum_outstanding field content is the sum of the two previous invoices

issue.title: Prevent domain field evaluation from failing when: (1) the domain is …
issue.body:
I have some code like this:
# In Python:
class AccountPaymentOrder(models.Model):
    _inherit = "account.payment.order"
    json_allowed_journals_domain = fields.Char(related="payment_mode_id.json_allowed_journals_domain")
# In XML:
<xpath expr="//field[@name='journal_id']" position="attributes">
    <attribute name="domain">json_allowed_journals_domain</attribute>
</xpath>

And form loading was failing when creating a new record, because the fiels payment_mode_id was not yet set.

This pull request fixes this:
Prevent domain field evaluation from failing when: (1) the domain is given
by a related field and (2) the path to the target field is not yet
traversable. In this cases, reading the field from javascript code will
yield false. This fix makes the frontend assume a "[]" domain whenever the
field refered to in domain="" attribute contains a false value.

  - invoice a part of the global amount, open it (invoice_lines must match with order_lines)

  - create a new invoice, open it
  => sum_outstanding field content is the sum of the two previous invoices

issue.body:
Finish  #2 

### Clean and refactor

- [x] some clean. remove commented code :  https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/9582751d0e9db6de1706527209665fd322703810, remove "cagnotte" word : https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/8100b55f836a91adf5853f2af20b9cc84c8a99ea remove ``openupgradelib`` dependency : https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/6f6392ddcaac00eefb52c792e344760f28215914
- [x] rename file that contains view to fit OCA convention. https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/6de4402b564b34749fb827efd1ed577520c402c0 https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/10acc32dfb60035004117186cc0de92132e041d7
- [x] remove duplicated views for ``account.move`` and ``account.move.line`` https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/c94432c55cecf4fa9aedbd1548ed38626190c7bc https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/b49885ab1cd9375ee0b26a1afd4d84065a0d3aae  
- [x] refactor test functions to factorize code. https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/2887ce5b37b19d0621c2aaf17c54d0fce968e162
- [x] rename ``no_anonymous`` field into ``automatic_nominative_creation`` because the description is better, to have the possibility to introduce a new field ``only_nominative`` and to prevent double negation : https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/0d0e39214ae9cb96174abc0e6dc397c2a6bad933 (openupgrade script included).

### UX Improvment
- [x] add domain on product field of ``account.wallet.type`` https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/73f2bb4dc892e7f510b5dce50e3ae86f3e75a10f

### Bugfixes
- [x] in initial version, wallet balance are computed on draft, posted and cancel account move lines. With that patch, only 'posted' move lines impact balance. https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/6b8c6d794ffce550c9810bd7c3ddd5f6b9f0b49e
- [x] allow to select wallet on payment refund https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/f009d9030b7923067fe809b4ba3fb2b08f6e1e1e

### Add Feature
- [x] add field ``only_nominative`` on ``account.wallet.type`` to prevent wallet without partner defined. https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/e8c4fa380283197ede73bdac8202882cfd6eeb88
- [x] allow to select wallet on the wizard ``account.payment.register`` https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/223e7ef1ec464942ac3b7016f06f5a03da8ede91 
- [x] make credit note wallet feature working in a multi company and or multi wallet type context https://github.com/OCA/wallet/pull/9/commits/c23d67b2bfb43a0c1d20ccb136aa921483e4b94e

- basic test:
  - create a sale order with several products
  - invoice a part of the global amount, open it (invoice_lines must match with order_lines)

  - create a new invoice, open it
  => sum_outstanding field content is the sum of the two previous invoices

Before coding, it is recommended to create an issue to discuss the problem or feature
you want to add. If you did not, don't worry, we can discuss on the PR too.

commit for the test so we one see that your test reproduces the bug and is fixed by the
PR.

MIS Builder is actively maintained for Odoo versions 9, 10, 11 and 12.

If your feature is applicable with the same implementation to all these versions, please

In the rare cases your feature or implementation is specific to an Odoo version, then

been closed, but it is not of interest to users). The changelog entry must be reasonably
short and phrased in a way that is understandable by end users.

issue.title: Prevent domain field evaluation from failing when: (1) the domain is …
issue.body:
I have some code like this:
# In Python:
class AccountPaymentOrder(models.Model):
    _inherit = "account.payment.order"
    json_allowed_journals_domain = fields.Char(related="payment_mode_id.json_allowed_journals_domain")
# In XML:
<xpath expr="//field[@name='journal_id']" position="attributes">
    <attribute name="domain">json_allowed_journals_domain</attribute>
</xpath>

And form loading was failing when creating a new record, because the fiels payment_mode_id was not yet set.

This pull request fixes this:
Prevent domain field evaluation from failing when: (1) the domain is given
by a related field and (2) the path to the target field is not yet
traversable. In this cases, reading the field from javascript code will
yield false. This fix makes the frontend assume a "[]" domain whenever the
field refered to in domain="" attribute contains a false value.
